Catalogue
of the Lepidoptera of Belgium
Notodontidae
Noctuidae
Lymantriidae

The family includes well over 21000 described species, is worldwide in distribution, and particularly well developed in the tropics. The classification of the family is still uncertain. Hermiinae may be excluded from the Noctuidae in the future (Scoble 1992: 336).
Identification: Bretherton, Goater & Lorimer 1979, 1983, Buszko 1980, 1983, 1985, Fibiger 1990, 1993, 1997, Forster & Wohlfahrt 1971, Goater, Ronkay & Fibiger 2003, Hacker et al. 2002, Koch 1972, Kostrowicki 1956, 1959, Nowacki 1998, Ronkay & Ronkay 1994, 1995, Ronkay et al. 2001, Skinner 1984, Skou 1991.
Nomenclature according to Fauna Europaea.
Species in Belgium: 388.
